  • Field Details

    • scroll

      protected final JScrollPane scroll
      The JScrollPane that serves as the container for the panel displaying selected items.

      This scroll pane is customized to provide horizontal scrolling for the selected items and to maintain a compact height. It includes FlatLaf styling for consistent integration with the application's theme.

    • panel

      protected final JPanel panel
      The JPanel used to display the selected items in the combo box editor.

      This panel is initialized with a MigLayout, allowing flexible arrangement of the items. Each selected item is dynamically added or removed from this panel based on user interactions.

  • Constructor Details

    • ComboBoxMultiCellEditor

      public ComboBoxMultiCellEditor()
      Constructs a new ComboBoxMultiCellEditor. This editor is customized to display multiple selected items within a scrollable panel.

      The editor contains a JScrollPane that holds a JPanel. The panel is used to dynamically display the selected items. Styling is applied using FlatLaf properties for a consistent look and feel with the application's theme.

      • The scroll pane has a fixed height of 20 pixels and horizontal scrolling enabled.
      • Custom styles are applied to the scroll bar to match the FlatLaf design guidelines.
      • The panel is initialized with a MigLayout for flexible arrangement of items.
